James Gosling initiated Java language project in June 1991(OAK->Green->Java)

Write Once Run Anywhere

Features
Open Source-we can view the development code of JDK
Object Oriented-inheritance,polymorphism, encapsulation,abstraction
Platform Independent-Write Once Run Anywhere
Simple-No pointers,templates are removed
Secure-Class Loader,Byte Code Converter,Security Manager
Architecture-neutral-memory allocation on any platform is same size unlike C
Portable-because platform independency we can change one to another platform
Robust-Memory HAndling,Exception Handling
Multithreaded-for gaming applications
High Performance-JIT compiler
Distributed-Web based or desktop(zoom app)
Dynamic-adapt to evolving environment can carry extensive amount of runtime info


